        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1781903511" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8731578088189752587"><i>&apos;Don&apos;t try to seek equality between man and woman. </i><br/><br/><b>Simply because it does not exist!&apos;</b><br/><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1476262936i/20818879._SX540_.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>It&apos;s middle of the twentieth century.<br/>Struggle for Independence in India is at its peak. People, old or young are either becoming civil servants or freedom fighters - &apos;krantikari&apos;, with only one ambition in their mind - <b>To serve their Motherland.</b><br/><br/>Renuka Pal&apos;s story is not different from this. <br/>Well educated, sharp, honest and fearless, 15 years old, is dreaming of freeing her country from outsider&apos;s paw.<br/><br/>Renuka, who</span>
  <span id="freeText8731578088189752587" style="display:none"><i>'Don't try to seek equality between man and woman. </i><br><br><b>Simply because it does not exist!'</b><br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1476262936i/20818879._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>It's middle of the twentieth century.<br>Struggle for Independence in India is at its peak. People, old or young are either becoming civil servants or freedom fighters - 'krantikari', with only one ambition in their mind - <b>To serve their Motherland.</b><br><br>Renuka Pal's story is not different from this. <br>Well educated, sharp, honest and fearless, 15 years old, is dreaming of freeing her country from outsider's paw.<br><br>Renuka, who wants to be a doctor to serve her country, is shattered that her dreams are not coming true anymore. She ends up marrying in a zamindaar's family. <br><br>Strict rules, mysterious talks and true to the core gossips spread in the neighborhood about the lineage of Zamindaar's are some of the major traits of this family and are not hidden to anyone. <br><br><i>Except Her. </i><br><br>She accepts her fate, that whatever it may come, she'll fight with it all. <br><br>The Curse that has bestowed upon her in-law's ancestors will not spare anyone who gets related to that family. <br><br>Generations by generations, Damini's curse will prevail.<br><br>But who is Damini? <br>Why is not anyone comfortable when Renuka asks to meet her mother-in-law? <br>Why everyone is hiding something or other? <br><br>Questions! Questions! Questions!<br><br>But Renuka is not to be stopped until she figures out the root cause of all the problems she has to face. <br>Will her curiosity not lead her to death? <br>Will she not get the destiny of an every day woman's life? <br><br>Remarks from her own mother, learning about the heinous acts by her in-laws' ancestors, watching the tragic story of every woman in her family.<br>Will she not get the same fate? <br>or <br><i>Will she survive it all, to write the story from a <b>'Survivor's Perspective' </b>?</i><br><br>The Curse of Damini is a supersonic attempt that supports the quote very well, that ALL CURSES ARE MEANT TO BE BROKEN.<br><br>Writing Historical-Mystery-Fiction is a Herculean task in itself and weaving it in a heartbreaking manner.<br><br><b>THAT moved me and so will it to anyone. </b></span>
